This paper is likely to belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) category as it deals with natural language semantics. It may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category as it discusses the concept of monads, which is a mathematical structure used in machine learning. Additionally, it could be classified under Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) as it deals with the representation of meaning in natural language. The paper also discusses compositionality, which is a key concept in Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Software Engineering (cs.SE), making these categories also likely candidates.
